The paper deals with graph modification problems, which are a common topic in computer science and can be categorized under several sub-fields. The use of forbidden induced subgraphs to characterize graph properties suggests that the paper may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. The focus on parameterized complexity and kernelization techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) or Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories. Finally, the use of cographs and P4-free graphs as examples suggests that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
